  "text": "Researchers use topology to study intrinsic geometric properties of objects that do not depend on a chosen set of coordinates and this process also has been employed in the analysis of dance patterns [CITATION_1] . This approach provides very useful notions for interpreting movement data generated by musical performance gestures. In fact, such body movements are bound to multimodal expressive features, which are inherently qualitative.",
